Automated Learning and Discovery Stat-Of-The-Art and Research Topics in a Rapidly Growing Field
 Abstract This report summarizes the CONALD meeting, which took place June 11-13, 1998, at Carnegie Mellon University.  CONALD brought together an interdisciplinary group of scientists, concerned with decision making based on data.  This report is organized in two parts.  The first part (pages 1-6) summarizes the CONALD meeting and highlights its main outcomes, beyond the individual workshop level.  The second part (pages 7-30) summarize the results obtained in the individual workshops, discussing in depth promising research topics.
